The then defence secretary John Reid said he hoped 'not a shot would be fired' in what was expected to be a three-year campaign.

But violence spiralled and hundreds of troops have been killed by bullets and roadside bombs. The war has claimed 448 UK lives.

A few hundred soldiers will remain on standby to carry out strike operations if requested by the Afghans.

